MAHIKENG - The North West ministerial task team is visiting the province to address several issues. 
	
	Cabinet has invoked a section of the Constitution, allowing national government to intervene when provinces fail to meet Constitutional obligations. READ: Inter-ministerial task team to probe governance in protest-riddled North West The task team's main purpose is to address the ongoing health crisis and violent protests that have rocked the province. It will present a report to Cabinet on Wednesday. eNCA